The whole idea of the game is good, a survival game where you gather resources to craft things to gather resources better, but with the added dinosaur that you tame and breed to fight for you, but it has some deep flaws that make me not recommend it:
- While the communication is generally good, some things are specially terrible, like how you can't bring some dinos to a boss, and you'll only know about it once you're teleported to the boss without these dinos;
- About the non-dedicated session, it's terrible to play with friends if you don't have a dedicated server, because even though the tether distance is configurable, since the caves and bosses are in a separate "instance" from the rest of the world, whenever the host enters one of them everyone else gets instantly teleported there;
- The whole game also feels deeply unfair to me, even though you can configure how grindy the game is with the sliders before starting the game, some things you can only be fixed with mods, like how the thieving wild dinos can steal and eat a whole stack of meat from you at once, or how many dinos can take you off your mount without any real way to prevent that other than avoid them, or how you need a very RNG-based recipe to create a better quality piece of equipment;

I did have some fun playing this game, but all these issues (and a few minor ones I didn't mention) were really detrimental to my experience, and the simple fact that I bought this game to play with friends and the tethering alone gave us a lot of trouble, I can't recommend it.

